If it doesn't work out again, I know something is up haha.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/2xQcXFN.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Anyway, got this beautiful dusty pink velvet fabric at a local fabric store and immediately knew I wanted to make something cute</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/lRpJU3z.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Skirt part almost done. Added some frills because I love that</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/60SepVz.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The base of the top. I went for a kind of a simplified bustier vibe for it</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/rLwKvG5.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Top of part  almost done! More frills added!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/MrKKGuB.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Pinning together bottom and top</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/7sltWiz.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The waistline came out a bit uneven, I've fixed that since, just haven't taken any new pictures</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/elg4xuc.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Oh, and I added a pentagram! I was looking around everywhere for some elastic bands in the the same shade as the fabric, didn't have any luck, so I went with a dusty lilac instead</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/pXzdGp1.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I like this dress a lot and have already worn it a few times!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/b0AeDye</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Miiaka]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>'Merica.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Un9xFIr</link><de